<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Star" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Star</orth> (masc. in <bibl n="shak. ven 861" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 861</bibl>) a celestial body shining in the night: <bibl n="shak. ven 861" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 861</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ven 861" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 861</bibl> <bibl n="shak. luc 164" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 164</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. luc 164" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 164</bibl> <bibl n="shak. son 132.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 132, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.6.9" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. II, 6, 9</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 3.1.156" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 156</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.3.101" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 3, 101</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 4.2.219" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. IV, 2, 219</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 4.3.231" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 3, 231</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.205" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 205</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.407" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. III, 2, 407</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 4.5.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 5, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 4.5.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 5, 7</bibl> <bibl n="shak. aww 1.1.97" default="NO" valid="yes">All's I, 1, 97</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.48" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 48</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.48" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 48</bibl> <bibl n="shak. wt 5.1.206" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 206</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 3.13.95" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 13, 95</bibl> etc. <cit><quote>the seven --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.2.16" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 2, 16</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.4.201" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 4, 201</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 1.5.38" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 5, 38</bibl>. <cit><quote>fixed s.</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 1.1.89" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL I, 1, 89</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the north s.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 2.1.258" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 1, 258</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>the northern s.</quote> <bibl n="shak. jc 3.1.60" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. III, 1, 60</bibl></cit>. <emph>the watery s.</emph> (the moon) <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.1" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 1</bibl>; <cit><quote>the moist s.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 1.1.118" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 1, 118</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a blazing s.</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 1.3.91" default="NO" valid="yes">All's I, 3, 91</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a falling s.</quote> <bibl n="shak. h8 4.1.55" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 IV, 1, 55</bibl></cit>; cf. <bibl n="shak. ant 4.14.106" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. IV, 14, 106</bibl>. <cit><quote>a shooting s.</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 2.4.19" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 II, 4, 19</bibl></cit>; cf. <bibl n="shak. ven 815" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 815</bibl>; <bibl n="shak. luc 1525" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1525</bibl>; <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.1.153" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 1, 153</bibl>; <bibl n="shak. ham 1.5.17" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 5, 17</bibl>. Brilliant things called <emph>--s;</emph> especially bright eyes: <bibl n="shak. luc 13" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 13</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. son 14.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 14, 10</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 5.1.67" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. V, 1, 67</bibl>. Or persons of brilliant qualities: <bibl n="shak. pht 51" default="NO" valid="yes">Phoen. 51</bibl>. H5 Epil. <bibl n="shak. pht 51" default="NO" valid="yes">Phoen. 51</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.2.144" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 2, 144</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 2.2.102" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 II, 2, 102</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 4.1.54" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 IV, 1, 54</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 1.2.25" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 2, 25</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 4.14.106" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. IV, 14, 106</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 5.2.311" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 311</bibl>. Eminent persons made --s after their death: <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.1.55" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 1, 55</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.5.352" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 5, 352</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 5.3.79" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. V, 3, 79</bibl>. cf. <bibl n="shak. rom 3.2.22" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 2, 22</bibl>.<lb />Influencing human fortune: <bibl n="shak. son 14.1" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 14, 1</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 3.25.1" default="NO" valid="yes">25, 1</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 3.26.9" default="NO" valid="yes">26, 9</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 1.2.182" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. I, 2, 182</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.7.74" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. II, 7, 74</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 2.1.349" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 1, 349</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 3.79" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL III, 79</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.394" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 394</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 4.5.40" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 5, 40</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 1.1.197" default="NO" valid="yes">All's I, 1, 197</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 1.1.197" default="NO" valid="yes">All's I, 1, 197</bibl> <bibl n="shak. aww 1.3.252" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 3, 252</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 2.5.80" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 5, 80</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 1.3.142" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. I, 3, 142</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 2.1.3" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 1, 3</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 2.5.156" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 5, 156</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 2.5.156" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 5, 156</bibl> <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.363" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 363</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 3.1.126" default="NO" valid="yes">John III, 1, 126</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 4.21" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 IV, 21</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.1.4" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 1, 4</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 4.5.6" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 5, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.1.206" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 1, 206</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 4.6.22" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C IV, 6, 22</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.7.172" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 7, 172</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 4.4.215" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 215</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 1.4.107" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. I, 4, 107</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 5.1.24" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 24</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 5.3.111" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 111</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 1.2.140" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. I, 2, 140</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.4.32" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 4, 32</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 4.3.35" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. IV, 3, 35</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 3.13.145" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. III, 13, 145</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 5.4.105" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. V, 4, 105</bibl> <emph>(Jovial s.)</emph> etc. <cit><quote>Lord Hamlet is a prince, out of thy s.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 2.2.141" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. II, 2, 141</bibl></cit> (above thee in fortune).
<lb />== loadstar: <emph>it</emph> (love) <cit><quote>is the s. to every wandering bark,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 116.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 116, 7</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>there's no more sailing by the s.</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 3.4.58" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado III, 4, 58</bibl></cit>. cf. <bibl n="shak. son 26.9" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 26, 9</bibl> and <bibl n="shak. aww 2.1.57" default="NO" valid="yes">All's II, 1, 57</bibl>.
